<div class="textblock"><p>Best practices for designing the Main Menu for your Free-to-Play games.</p>
<h1><a class="anchor" id="f2p_mm_intro"></a>
Main Menu Design and Big Fish Required Elements</h1>
<p>Main Menu best practices are critically important to your game. A great Main Menu makes a great first impression and sets the tone of quality and ease-of-use for your game.</p>
<p>Overall, your Main Menu should be thoughtfully designed and use appealing visuals to welcome the player to your game.</p>
<p>Although there are no specific placement standards for incorporating required Big Fish elements on your Main Menu, they <em>must</em> appear somewhere in your game.</p>
<h2><a class="anchor" id="f2p_mm_inc_elements"></a>
Incorporating Big Fish elements in design</h2>
<p>When possible, use in-game art or UI elements as buttons instead of plain text or text boxes.</p>
<p>Buttons that are integrated into the art, and match the look and feel of the game, make for a cohesive and engaging Main Menu. A great main menu will offer no barriers to entry and provide no room for confusion.</p>
<ul>
<li>When possible, use in-game art or UI elements as buttons instead of plain text or text boxes.</li>
<li>Button style matches graphic design features (theme, scenery, characters, etc.).</li>
<li>Avoid unnecessary clutter. Simplicity increases the clarity of the message to, “Play our game!” Players should easily find and tap on the button they want.</li>
</ul>
<h2><a class="anchor" id="f2p_mm_Login"></a>
Sign In button</h2>
<p>Big Fish Login is an interface that lets users sign in to their Big Fish accounts inside a Big Fish app. Call [<a href="interfacebfg_login_controller.html#a5ea88a700c4b6280c35f1b60b1f68a88" class="el">bfgLoginController isLoggedIn</a>] to determine whether to show <b>Sign In</b> or <b>Sign Out</b>. You can get a fully formed UIButton from the SDK or build your own button out of images also provided by the SDK.</p>
<p>For more information, see <a class="el" href="reference_class.html#bfgLoginImplementation">Implementing Big Fish Login</a>.</p>
<dl class="section note"><dt>Note</dt><dd><ul>
<li>Login is an optional feature. Discuss with your Big Fish Producer whether you should implement Big Fish Login in your game, and where to place the <b>Sign In/Sign Out</b> buttons.</li>
<li>You are responsible for adding the Sign In button to your view hierarchy.</li>
</ul>
</dd></dl>
<p>Also see <a class="el" href="reference_class.html#rc_bfgLogin">Big Fish Login</a>.</p>
<h2><a class="anchor" id="f2p_mm_rating"></a>
Rating buttons</h2>
<p>Free-to-Play games implement rating prompts on a case-by-case basis. For information specific to your game, contact your Big Fish Producer.</p>
<p>Ratings buttons engage the user to evaluate games. There are three types you can use to prompt the user for reviews and other feedback:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Main Menu rating prompt</b>: Appears after the user pauses and resumes game play.</li>
<li><b>In-game rating prompt</b>: Appears at strategic points in the game's progress.</li>
<li><b>Like [Game Title]?</b>: Launches a pop-up. May appear at the end of a game session, after the user pauses and resumes game play. If there is no planned sequel for your game, then the rating button should read: <b>Like [Game Title]?</b></li>
</ul>
<p>The <a class="el" href="interfacebfg_rating.html" title="Enables users to rate games. ">bfgRating</a> class implements game rating. The <a class="el" href="interfacebfg_game_reporting.html" title="Required game logging APIs. ">bfgGameReporting</a> class has several events that track this feature.</p>
<p>Also see <a class="el" href="reference_class.html#rc_bfgRating">Rating - bfgRating</a>.</p>
<h3><a class="anchor" id="ratings_json"></a>
bfg_default_settings.json ratings settings</h3>
<p>For a generic game rating notification, use the rating keys in the <b>bfg_default_settings.json</b> file copied from the <b>bfglib_gamespecific_resources</b> directory.</p>
<p>In <b>bfg_default_settings.json</b>, values can be set for the <b>rating_days_until_prompt</b> and <b>rating_uses_until</b> prompt parameters. These should be left at the default unless you are directed otherwise by your Big Fish Producer. The ratings prompt appears after the set number of days or game uses, regardless of the progress within the game. Prompts based on these parameters will not display in active games until the user returns to the Main Menu, or the user removes the game from the multi-tasking tray.</p>
<h3><a class="anchor" id="Main_menu_rating"></a>
Main Menu rating prompt</h3>
<p>The Main Menu rating prompt encourages users to rate a game. Tapping the button from the Main Menu displays a pop-up promoting the user to rate the game.</p>
<ul>
<li>Use the [<a href="interfacebfg_rating.html#ada82cbb76d090204f6bd5305e75aa501" class="el">bfgRating canShowMainMenuRateButton</a>] API to display this button.</li>
<li>You <em>must</em> provide the art assets for the button and pop-up, and submit those assets to your Big Fish Producer for approval.</li>
<li>Call the Big Fish [<a href="interfacebfg_rating.html#ad284cb377269073f1182867c4c82fbdb" class="el">bfgRating mainMenuRateApp</a>] API to navigate the user to the correct iTunes page to rate your app.</li>
</ul>
<dl class="section note"><dt>Note</dt><dd>Your game may or may not require a Main Menu rating prompt. For more information, contact your Big Fish Producer.</dd></dl>
<h3><a class="anchor" id="f2p_In_game_rating"></a>
In-game rating prompt</h3>
<p>The in-game rating prompt may appear at a natural point in the game, based on the completion of game levels or mini-games, or after a few scenes in a hidden object game.</p>
<ul>
<li>Set the <b>rating_significant_events_until_prompt</b> key in <b>bfg_default_settings.json</b> to the number of significant events that must be triggered before the game displays the in-game ratings prompt.</li>
</ul>
<div class="image">
<img src="ratingnotification.jpg" alt="ratingnotification.jpg"/>
</div>
<p>The rating provides the following options:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Rate <em style="color:red">game_name</em></b> takes the user to the App Store to rate the game. The in-game rating prompt and Main Menu rating prompt stop appearing.</li>
<li><b>Remind me later</b> reminds the user again at another point in the game.</li>
<li><b>No thank you!</b> sets a flag that stops rating prompts from appearing.</li>
</ul>
<h3><a class="anchor" id="f2p_mm_like"></a>
Like [Game Title]? pop-up</h3>
<p>If the <b>Like [Game Title]?</b> button is tapped, a pop-up with content from the current game should appear.</p>
<div class="image">
<img src="likegame_popup_new.jpg" alt="likegame_popup_new.jpg"/>
</div>
<ul>
<li><b>“Enjoying [Current Game Title]?”:</b> This should be the full title.</li>
<li><b>“Let us know, rate it now!”:</b> This sentence can be in all caps or lower case.</li>
<li><b>“Rate it Now!” button:</b> When tapped, the button will call the [<a href="interfacebfg_rating.html#ad284cb377269073f1182867c4c82fbdb" class="el">bfgRating mainMenuRateApp</a>] API, and take the player directly to the App Store to rate the game or write a review. Once this button is tapped, it should no longer appear on the Main Menu.</li>
<li>An <b>"X"</b> button in the top right corner should also be included to close the pop-up.</li>
</ul>
<h2><a class="anchor" id="f2p_more_games"></a>
More Games button</h2>
<p>All games <em>must</em> include a <b>More Games</b> button on the Main Menu.</p>
<ul>
<li>Calls the [<a href="interfacebfg_manager.html#a0f7b15d1862eaca88de68a9f48a6d8a8" class="el">bfgRating showMoreGames</a>] API when a user taps the <b>More Games</b> button.</li>
<li>Launches a More Games UI.</li>
<li>The Big Fish logo should be visible on the <b>More Games</b> button, but otherwise the style of this button should match the Main Menu style.</li>
<li>Ask your Big Fish Producer for the most up-to-date logo assets when you are ready to create this button.</li>
</ul>
<p>Also see <a class="el" href="reference_class.html#more_games_bfgManager">More Games - bfgManager showMoreGames</a>.</p>
<h2><a class="anchor" id="f2p_mm_support"></a>
Support button</h2>
<p>All games <em>must</em> include a <b>Support</b> button. Tapping the <b>Support</b> button opens a Web browser in the game that displays a mobile games help article on <a href="http://bigfishgames.custhelp.com/app/home" class="el" target="_blank">bigfishgames.com</a>.</p>
<ul>
<li>Add the <b>Support</b> button in the style of your game and call the [<a href="interfacebfg_manager.html#a36dc0bd019902e9cf816c926e66bf8f0" class="el">bfgManager showSupport</a>] API.</li>
</ul>
<h2><a class="anchor" id="f2p_mm_privacy_policy"></a>
Privacy Policy button</h2>
<p>All games <em>must</em> include a <b>Privacy Policy</b> button. Tapping the <b>Privacy Policy</b> button opens a Web browser in the game that displays the full Privacy Policy on <a href="http://www.bigfishgames.com/company/privacy.html" class="el" target="_blank">bigfishgames.com</a>.</p>
<ul>
<li>Add the <b>Privacy Policy</b> button in the style of your game and call the [<a href="interfacebfg_manager.html#ace61025e839f1298ebc3c78307dd3791" class="el">bfgManager showPrivacy</a>] API.</li>
</ul>
<dl class="section note"><dt>Note</dt><dd>This API launches a localized version of the Privacy Policy page. Games without a localized version should use the English version (e.g., Russian or Chinese).</dd></dl>
<h2><a class="anchor" id="f2p_mm_terms_use"></a>
Terms of Use button</h2>
<p>All games <em>must</em> include a <b>Terms of Use</b> button. Tapping the <b>Terms of Use</b> button opens a Web browser in the game that displays the full Terms of Use on <a href="http://www.bigfishgames.com/company/terms.html" class="el" target="_blank">bigfishgames.com</a>.</p>
<ul>
<li>Add the <b>Terms of Use</b> button in the style of your game and call the [<a href="interfacebfg_manager.html#a8e7c1a2dab58d6921c67cef2fdb6b130" class="el">bfgManager showTerms</a>] API.</li>
</ul>
<dl class="section note"><dt>Note</dt><dd>This API launches a localized version of the Terms of Use page. Games without a localized version should use the English version (e.g., Russian or Chinese).</dd></dl>
<h2><a class="anchor" id="f2p_mm_copyright_legal"></a>
Copyright and legal text</h2>
<p>All games <em>must</em> include the default copyright for the current calendar year. Big Fish franchise games and owned intellectual property must also include trademarks for the game or franchise.</p>
<ul>
<li>Default copyright text:</li>
</ul>
 
    <table border=1 cellspacing=0><tr>
        <td>&copy;2014 Big Fish Games, Inc. Big Fish, and the Big Fish logo are trademarks of Big Fish Games, Inc.
            Version Number <i style=color:red>XX.XX.XX</i></td></tr></table>
<ul>
<li>Example of copyright text for a franchise game or owned intellectual property:</li>
</ul>
 
    <table border=1 cellspacing=0><tr>
        <td>&copy;2014 Big Fish Games, Inc. Big Fish, the Big Fish logo, and &lt;Franchise Name or Game Name&gt; are trademarks of Big Fish Games, Inc.
Version Number<i style=color:red>XX.XX.XX</i></td></tr></table>
<ul>
<li>Replace <i style=color:red>XX.XX.XX</i>  with the current build version number. For more information about build version numbers, see <a class="el" href="production.html#Versioning">Versioning</a>.</li>
</ul>
<h2><a class="anchor" id="f2p_mm_credits"></a>
Credits</h2>
<p>Credits for your game are optional. For Big Fish Studios titles only, contact your Big Fish Producer to see if you must include Big Fish credits.</p>
<h2><a class="anchor" id="f2p_mm_sliders"></a>
Sound sliders</h2>
<p>All sound sliders should conform to Apple guidelines and default to 70%. For more information, see the <a class="el" href="f2p_usability.html#usability_audio">Audio</a> usability requirements. </p>
